{"author":{"id":"daecaa79b752289d08fa06c7a65c8d0387caf00b7e262b5741f4805727d0a582"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1592413202,"nonce":"pWSH0CMcma2/jPslV5ITQkT4UDo=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY0NTQ5Nzk4NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/406#issuecomment-645497985"},"message":"Yeah, if you have the follow file structure:\n\n**`~/.gitconfig`**\n\n```\n[include]\n  path = \"~/.gitconfig.local\"\n```\n\n**`~/.gitconfig.local`**\n\n```\n[foo]\n  bar = \"baz\"\n```\n\nthen `git config --get foo.bar` returns `baz` as expected, however explicitly defining `--global` doesn't follow the `include` statement and thus will return an empty value.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1592413250,"nonce":"14N7eeKz28Xeu/cE+vy45NU9d1M=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY0NTQ5ODQyMA==","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/406#issuecomment-645498420"},"message":"`git-bug` should probably not care about where the credentials are coming from and rely upon Git's configuration loading by simply calling:\n\n```\ngit config --get \u003ckey...\u003e\n```\n\ninstead of explicitly calling `--global`, `--local`, or `--system`.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1592413295,"nonce":"tVOl6P4GwfiFRaRN3cp4IDfRV5U=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY0NTQ5ODgxNA==","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/406#issuecomment-645498814"},"message":"I don't have time to familiarize myself with the codebase today, but this is a fairly trivial patch (if you approve of it) and I'd be happy to take care of this over the next few days / weekend.","files":null}]}